OL,3,CSchool proven to have discriminated
OL,4,Cagainst a child with disabilites
OL,6,FDespite this, the Tribunal ruled that
OL,7,Fthe school failed to provide the child
OL,8,Fwith the technology they needed for
OL,9,Flearning, did not support them with
OL,10,Fhomework, and excluded them from a
OL,11,Flesson.
OL,13,FSpeaking to ITV News anonymously, the
OL,14,Fchild's mother says: "From a very
OL,15,Fyoung age, my child said, 'But what
OL,16,Fabout me?'"
OL,18,FThe mother explains that the
OL,19,Fdiscrimination started when her child
OL,20,Fwas not allowed to join the breakfast
OL,21,Fclub.
