OL,3,CSchool proven to have discriminated
OL,4,Cagainst a child with disabilites
OL,6,FThe mother adds: "My child loves
OL,7,Flearning, and this was one of the
OL,8,Fproblems at the school, there was a
OL,9,Flot of talk about what my child needed
OL,10,Fand would need in later life, and they
OL,11,Freally struggled to grasp, in the
OL,12,Feducation department, the SEND
OL,13,Fdepartment and the school, that my
OL,14,Fchild does have a love for learning."
OL,16,FShe states that the child would feel
OL,17,Ffrustrated when their sibling would
OL,18,Fcome home from school with homework
OL,19,Fand says they would ask: "Where's my
OL,20,Fhomework, where are my spellings,
OL,21,Fwhere's my maths?"
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G6/13
