OL,4,Cagainst a child with disabilites
OL,6,FOn the Government hiring a top UK
OL,7,Fbarrister to represent them at the
OL,8,FTribunal, the mother says: "There was
OL,9,Fthat feeling of anger, of wasting
OL,10,Fmoney, especially as lots of the
OL,11,Fthings I had asked for my child to
OL,12,Fhave, that they were legally entitled
OL,13,Fto, were so cheap.
OL,15,F"The school was requesting funding
OL,16,Fbecause they're in a budget deficit
OL,17,Fand then the Law Officers Department
OL,18,Fare spending the vast sum of money on
OL,19,Fa UK barrister."
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G9/13
