OL,3,CSchool proven to have discriminated
OL,4,Cagainst a child with disabilites
OL,6,FWhilst the Tribunal did not agree with
OL,7,Fall of the mother's claims, including
OL,8,Fthat there was reduced access to the
OL,9,Fcurriculum, it did find the school
OL,10,Fguilty of failing to provide assistive
OL,11,Ftechnology, failing to provide
OL,12,Fdifferentiated homework and
OL,13,Fdiscrimination arising from disability.
OL,15,FIt noted that the child's Record of
OL,16,FNeed required assistive technology,
OL,17,Fbut the school failed to take
OL,18,Freasonable steps to ensure it could
OL,19,Factually be accessed or used in class.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws        G10/13
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
