PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F381A1767698618
OL,3,CSchool proven to have discriminated
OL,4,Cagainst a child with disabilites
OL,6,FIt added that simply having laptops
OL,7,F"available in boxes" was insufficient.
OL,9,FThe Tribunal also upheld that very
OL,10,Flittle differentiated homework was
OL,11,Fprovided, while staff evidence was
OL,12,Finconsistent, and this placed the
OL,13,Fchild at a substantial disadvantage.
OL,15,FThirdly, it found a specific incident
OL,16,Fwhere the child was excluded from a
OL,17,Flesson and instead shown videos,
OL,18,Famounting to unfavourable treatment
OL,19,Farising from disability.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws        G11/13
