PN,38113
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F381A1767698618
OL,3,CSchool proven to have discriminated
OL,4,Cagainst a child with disabilites
OL,6,F"We are pleased that the Tribunal did
OL,7,Fnot uphold any of the claims that
OL,8,Fthere is a non-inclusive attitude at
OL,9,Fthe school.
OL,11,F"We are also pleased that the Tribunal
OL,12,Ffound that all who were most
OL,13,Fresponsible for the pupil were acting
OL,14,Fin what they believed to be the
OL,15,Fpupil's best interests."
OL,17,FHowever, the child's mother says she
OL,18,Fis still waiting for an apology and
OL,19,Fwants action to be taken so all
OL,20,Ffamilies feel properly supported.
